  ],
  "dcterms:abstract": "Various neurophysiological and cognitive functions are based on transferring information between spiking neurons via a complex system of synaptic connections. This study explores the effects of synaptic transmission probability on the ability of the hippocampal place cell ensembles to produce a cognitive map of the environment using methods from algebraic topology.",
  "schema:datePublished": "2019-01-24",
  "schema:keywords": [
    "Neurophysiology",
    "Cognitive maps",
    "Synaptic connections",
    "Algebraic topology",
    "Hippocampal place cells"
  ],
